          <h2>Milton C. Shedd</h2>
          <p>SeaWorld first came into existence in San Diego in 1964 with the idea being that everyone would want to come see animals do tricks for a small ticket fee. Milton Shedd, one of the founders of SeaWorld, tried to make the park as environmentally friendly as possible as to eliminate any and all negativity from his park. According to The New York Times, "He loved being out, loved being a fisherman, but always felt you needed to go a step beyond, to put fish back into the ocean and not always be a taker.‚Äù </p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="#" role="button">View details &raquo;</a></p>
